{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Raise the unladen weight limit of dual purpose vehicles to reflect new vehicles.",
        "additional_details": "Due to the vast improvements made in safety design the weight of vehicles has increased significantly since the regulation published in 1986. As such I request that the weight limit is raised to accommodate new vehicles being produced and similar to that of passenger car\u2019s regularly exceeding 2.5 tonnes (eg range rovers).",
        "background": "As per \u201cThe Road Vehicles (Construction and Use) Regulations 1986\u201d a dual purpose vehicle can not exceed 2040kg unladen weight. I request that this limit is raised to accommodate new vehicles being produced; as many use vehicles such as pickups for daily non business use.",
